commit_message:
Adds Hortonworks Data Platform element to savanna-image-elements

This patch adds a new element, "hortonworks-hdp" to the
  savanna-image-elements project.  This element can be used to create
  Virtual Machine images that have the Hortonworks Data Platform (HDP)
  installed by default.
The element includes support for installing version 1.3 and 2.0 of the
  platform, and the README gives more details on how to configure this.
The patch also includes a bash script that creates several CentOS
  images with HDP pre-installed.  This script can either be used to
  generate the images as they are currently configured, or can be used
  as an example of how to use diskimage-builder to create qcow2 images
  with HDP.
This patch only supports generating CentOS images, and we could
  potentially add more supported platforms as time permits.

Implements: blueprint add-hdp-images-to-savanna-image-elements

Change-Id: I7108851f760147d379e82078cf390d7ff13d8898

commit_message:
Fix test_provider_token_expiration_validation transient failure

The keystone.tests.test_token_provider.TestTokenProvider.
test_provider_token_expiration_validation test would fail if the
tests weren't run before the sample token expired. This could
happen if the system was slow and the previous tests took a long
time causing a potential transient failure.

Change-Id: Ia662fcdc0cd26568fa8ea9f27d0a34cb1bfe46e6
Closes-Bug: #1278550

commit_message:
Remove explicit access to is_admin in context

is_admin should not be exlicitely accessed from code. Policies should be
used to check if it's set and context.elevated() to run something in
admin context.

Change-Id: I27754a378073844c3e24d94038a5d24f9a3c6dc3

commit_message:
Add scheduling specific task on sucess/error

 * Fix get task properties, get task in DSL
 * Evaluating task on success/error/finish properties in engine:
   - evaluate YAQL conditions
   - schedule tasks
 * Unit tests for handling success/error/finish

 * For real work with context there is need to store
   it somewhere

Implements: blueprint schedule-tasks-after-completion

commit_message:
Don't require passing in port_security=False if security_groups present

If creating a port on a network that is marked as port_security_enabled=False
and one passes in a security_group in the port_create request previously an
error was raised saying they needed to also pass in
port_security_enabled=False. This patch removes that requirement and instead
sets port_security_enabled=True internally if a port has an ip_address and a
security_group is passed in. This is more convient and does not break
backwards compatibility.

Closes-bug: #1267249
Change-Id: Ifb5a5511f016a5d8c5b5075c9fdc27279cdd9bb5

commit_message:
Cinder backups: add a note about flushing filesystems

LVM snapshots might contain corrupted data if the guest OS has not flushed dirty
buffers. Add a note to warn the admin about this.

Also use cinder-volumes as VG name, not nova-volumes.

Change-Id: If72dcc174523bfece74ed7f7617fbffe9cf51d60

commit_message:
Fix deprecation warnings in inline templates

The puppet-swift modules emit deprecation warnings of the form:

Warning: Variable access via 'pipeline' is deprecated. Use
  '@pipeline' instead. template[inline]:2
   (at (erb):2:in `result')

These are due to missing @ signs in inline ERB templates in
storage/server.pp and proxy.pp.  This patch fixes them.

Change-Id: I3745cfd86c4332f00bc10a0999088691b3833147
Closes-Bug: #1282717

commit_message:
RECOMMIT: Skip a test for nicira service plugin

test_router_add_interface_subnet_with_port_from_other_tenant
is causing intermittent failures in unit tests because of
issues related with sql session autoflush.

This patch skips this test, since it is already covered
by another test case in the same module. This should prevent
job failures while the relevant bug is addressed.

Change-Id: Ifbe28167b055ad8844351c5d2723a066f312bda0
Related-Bug: 1280035

commit_message:
Use "Expect: 100-continue" handshake during upload

During upload, if the Auth token is expired, the swift client
unnecessarily uploads the chunks and fails at the end.
Instead, we could have a fail fast mechanism using the
100-continue handshake. Only if the client receives a 100 continue
from swift, it should continue uploading the chunks.
Otherwise, if a 401 is received, it should fetch a fresh auth
token and retry the request.

Change-Id: I6e89085e763fe726b7653bade67d2b0b6eb6a056
implements-blueprint: should-use-100-continue-header
implements-blueprint: retry-auth-swift-uploads
Depends on: bp use-bufferedhttp-in-swiftclient

commit_message:
Move policy 'create:forced_host' into api layer

This patch move policy 'create:forced_host' into api layer
for ec2 and nova v2 api. And mova it into availability-zone extension
for nova v3 api. And rename it to follow v3 rules.

commit_message:
Policy-Based-Scheduler

This patch implements blueprint policy-based-scheduler. The policy-based
scheduler reads scheduling rules from policy repository and applies to each
target (availability-zones, aggregates, all) or each tenant. This patch uses
/etc/nova/scheduling_policy.json as a policy repository.

Rule format: <target> - <effect> - <condition>
Available effects and conditions are stored in nova/scheduler/policy_plugins
folder.

Change in host_manager.py to be able to precise which weighers to be used.
Add NbHostWeigher which uses number of active instances as note.

Change-Id: I5f3f557ea9b0adbd08116e6b15e7206bac602b18
Implements: blueprint policy-based-scheduler
DocImpact

commit_message:
Do valid check on volume status in roll_detaching

Roll_detaching API only take effect on detaching volume. While volume's
status is not detaching, cinder returns http 202 which would confuse
clients that the roll_detaching API is working backgroup. So doing valid
check on volume status in roll_detaching API.

Change-Id: I0470cd6361b59f72f6116edb38453c383f3718a3
Closes-bug: #1272820

commit_message:
Changes discoverable entry scope to 'compute:v3' for v3 core api

This patch changes the policy scope of core v3 api's discoverable entries
from 'compute_extension:v3' to 'compute:v3', also ensure extension_info
can work with core policy scope.

Also adds help function 'soft_core_authorizer' for core api policy check.

Partially implements bp v3-api-policy
DocImpact

Change-Id: Icf06ab0ad0dadb9b15fcd17c0eec280eabb4504c

commit_message:
netns_cleanup: stale ovs port ramains with use_ovs_veth=True

netns-cleanup doesn't delete corresponding ovs port.
So after running netns-cleanup, stale ovs ports remains.
So delete such ovs ports.
It uses ethtool which is not always available.
If it is not found, it falls back to previous behavior.

Change-Id: I474de1e788bad3caf31acd83382bb2ba0f780adf
Signed-off-by: Isaku Yamahata <yamahata@valinux.co.jp>

commit_message:
V3 Client Token Validation.

Implement token validation within the v3 client. Mostly based on the
functions extracted from auth_token middleware.

The V3 API does not expose the certificates that are used to sign PKI
tokens. We can't rely upon the V2 api being present or that we will have
access to it, so instead allow the certificates to be presented as data
or provided by a URL to be fetched. This URL will likely be to a V2
certificate source.

Part of bp keystoneclient-auth-token.

Change-Id: I90986c2a29ab6ab8b170530801647ffbd2c7ff01

change keystone endpoint-create default region

commit_message:
Refactor: move TrustNotFound to backends, not controller level

Currently, neither trust backend raises a TrustNotFound exception if
a trust is not found.

At the controller level, there are numerous checks to see if a
trust exists after a get_trust call, then raises TrustNotFound
if None.

This patch eliminates those calls by raising TrustNotFound
at the backend level.

Also, there is a TODO to change one case that previously
raised a 404 for an expired trust, this should probably raise
some sort of ExpiredTrust exception.

Updated another test to assert an exception is raised instead of
checking to see if None is returned, on a deleted trust.

Change-Id: I9767bb3d9f9b8b9890fdb17d03a90a82b6dca027

commit_message:
Skip nova v3 tests which create servers

In change I5c833731f1516c8256f835e21cc22fd613bc57ba the server post
response is being changed from returning the first created server to
a list of all created servers. In order for the API change to pass
Jenkins verification, server creates in v3 must be temporarily skipped.

commit_message:
Remove versionId, versionInfo, versionList from examples

I recall these attributes being discussed at one point
(pre-incubation?), but have never been supported by OpenStack and don't
appear to be defined in any v2.0 WADL/XSD specification.

Change-Id: I1aa1d7712318bd16e914ef47e1c5a26ecccb7d69
Closes-Bug: 1273831

commit_message:
refactor _get_list_limit() as a @property

There's no reason this needs to be an instance method, and drivers
should not be expected to have the attribute. This patch makes it an
optional attribute for drivers.

Change-Id: I6dd586ef09e52a6fa557d518d996f0a9bd731a41

commit_message:
Support installing Heat's contrib plugins

This adds support for enabling the three extra plugin types by defining
a comma delimited list like the following in your localrc.

HEAT_CONTRIB_PLUGINS=docker_plugin,rackspace

Note the list is empty by default.

Change-Id: I2c5ca54dd3e4aca931d0cdde79537c2c04555844

subject: WIP 3PAR Zone target map
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-14 01:23:52.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/san/hp/hp_3par_fc.py'], 'message': 'WIP 3PAR Zone target map

This patch, which should NOT be merged, shows
how to add the initiator target map that the
Fibre Channel Zone Manager needs to automatically
zone up 2 endpoints.   Once the Zone Manager lands,
we will submit a new patch against the 2.0.0 HP
3par FC driver.

commit_message:
Fix the reporting of pass or fail in cert test

The backtick was causing the result code coming back
to always be something other than 0.  This always
makes the test say that the certification fails.
Removing backtick usage fixes this.

Closes-Bug: 1276867

Sometimes two correlated exception traces are observed in
the server log for the Neutron Server backed by NSX:
RequestTimeout (The nsx request has timed out) and
OperationalError (Lock wait timeout exceeded). This is
generally described by Guru Salvatore Orlando as the,
and I quote, the "infamous eventlet-mysql deadlock".

This patch tries to address the issue by adding a
cooperative yield in the nsx client code (it’s a good idea
to call sleep(0) occasionally in any case) and also by
avoiding the unnecessary spawning of another Greenthread

commit_message:
Fix request timeout errors during calls to NSX controller

Sometimes two correlated exception traces are observed in
the server log for the Neutron Server backed by NSX:
RequestTimeout (The nsx request has timed out) and
OperationalError (Lock wait timeout exceeded). This is
generally described by Guru Salvatore Orlando as the,
and I quote, the "infamous eventlet-mysql deadlock".

This patch tries to address the issue by adding a
cooperative yield in the nsx client code (it’s a good idea
to call sleep(0) occasionally in any case) and also by
avoiding the unnecessary spawning of another Greenthread
within a call that is already executed in Greenthred
itself.

Closes-bug: #1267101
Related-bug: #1279497

Change-Id: I8e298468fb730f11a66fbd4211121ee7d3e2a548

commit_message:
Add ability to create provider networks (vlan,flat).

Provider network map directly to an existing physical network in
a data center. It's routable by default. Neutron v2.0 API implements
it using Provider Networks Neutron API Extension. This is different
from tenant network(implemented by 'OS::Neutron::Net'resource) and has
different requirements.

This ('OS::Neutron::ProviderNet') resource leverages additional
attributes as listed below from Neutron API extension.

provider:network_type - Specifies the nature of the physical network
mapped to this network resource. Examples are flat and vlan.

provider:physical_network - Identifies the physical network on top of
which this network object is being implemented.

provider:segmentation_id - Identifies an isolated segment on the
physical network.

Change-Id: Ic085d13c866722b0e6ed9fd7a4f43dd92d5b1a0b
Implements: blueprint neutron-net-resource-add-provider-network

revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-02-20 23:01:15.000000000', 'files': ['swift/obj/server.py', 'swift/common/utils.py', 'swift/common/middleware/slo.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_slo.py', 'test/unit/obj/test_server.py', 'swift/common/swob.py', 'swift/common/wsgi.py', 'swift/common/request_helpers.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_dlo.py', 'test/unit/common/test_swob.py', 'swift/common/middleware/dlo.py'], 'message': 'Support If-[None-]Match for object HEAD, SLO, and DLO

I moved the checking of If-Match and If-None-Match out of the object
server's GET method and into swob so that everyone can use it. The
interface is similar to the Range handling; make a response with
conditional_response=True, and you get handing of If-Match and
If-None-Match.

Since the only users of conditional_response are object GET, object
HEAD, SLO, and DLO, this has the effect of adding support for If-Match
and If-None-Match to just the latter three places and nowhere
else. This makes object GET and HEAD consistent for any kind of
object, large or small.

This also fixes a bug where various conditional headers (If-*) were
passed through to the object server on segment requests, which could
cause segment requests to fail with a 304 or 412 response. Now only
certain headers are copied to the segment requests, and that doesn't
include the conditional ones, so they can't goof up the segment
retrieval.

Note that I moved SegmentedIterable to swift.common.request_helpers
because it sprouted a transitive dependency on swob, and leaving it in
utils caused a circular import.

Bonus fix: unified the handling of DiskFileQuarantined and
DiskFileNotFound in object server GET and HEAD. Now in either case, a
412 will be returned if the client said "If-Match: *". If not, the
response is a 404, just like before.

commit_message:
Support If-[None-]Match for object HEAD, SLO, and DLO

I moved the checking of If-Match and If-None-Match out of the object
server's GET method and into swob so that everyone can use it. The
interface is similar to the Range handling; make a response with
conditional_response=True, and you get handing of If-Match and
If-None-Match.

Since the only users of conditional_response are object GET, object
HEAD, SLO, and DLO, this has the effect of adding support for If-Match
and If-None-Match to just the latter three places and nowhere
else. This makes object GET and HEAD consistent for any kind of
object, large or small.

This also fixes a bug where various conditional headers (If-*) were
passed through to the object server on segment requests, which could
cause segment requests to fail with a 304 or 412 response. Now only
certain headers are copied to the segment requests, and that doesn't
include the conditional ones, so they can't goof up the segment
retrieval.

Note that I moved SegmentedIterable to swift.common.request_helpers
because it sprouted a transitive dependency on swob, and leaving it in
utils caused a circular import.

Bonus fix: unified the handling of DiskFileQuarantined and
DiskFileNotFound in object server GET and HEAD. Now in either case, a
412 will be returned if the client said "If-Match: *". If not, the
response is a 404, just like before.

Closes-Bug: 1279076
Closes-Bug: 1280022
Closes-Bug: 1280028

Change-Id: Id2ee78346244d516b980202e990aa38ce6812de5

commit_message:
Remove duplicate configure-vm call in create-nodes

create-nodes duplicated the entire configure-vm call based on the
setting of $BRIDGE, to add an argument. There is an existing pattern for
that behaviour which means complex command lines don't have to be
duplicated.

Change-Id: I0f843b0be36aa13644953099cc109dee8d5e2ab3

commit_message:
feat(v1.1): Implement /ping endpoint for v1.1

This patch creates a new endpoint /ping in v1.1 API, which is a
clone of the /health endpoint in v1.0. Because a new /health
endpoint will be added in v1.1 to return more detailed KPI of
Marconi server.

Implement blueprint: api-v1.1-ping-endpoint

commit_message:
Fix resource mapping for Rackspace

resource_mapping() always returns all existing resource names and
their classes. available_resource_mapping() takes the dependencies
into account and only returns the ones whose dependencies have been
met.

In some unit tests we were passing data to handle_update() that had not
been passed through Stack.resolve_static_data() and getting away with it

Change-Id: I08b968b2a83fd3c1f0af97e62ea4745c87c24652

commit_message:
unit tests: Always resolve static functions

In some unit tests we were passing data to handle_update() that had not
been passed through Stack.resolve_static_data() and getting away with it
because it contained only runtime functions. With the move to only one
kind of function, this is no longer sufficient.

Change-Id: I08b968b2a83fd3c1f0af97e62ea4745c87c24652

Change-Id: I5621c9bd1ef7686f5cf321e39e1a457f31d0783d

commit_message:
Evaluate lazy functions in autoscaling launch config

Instead of just copying an autoscaling launch config, first resolve any
lazily-evaluated functions by calling function.resolve(). This also has
the same effect as doing copy.deepcopy() for our purposes, so there is no
need to do both.

Change-Id: I5621c9bd1ef7686f5cf321e39e1a457f31d0783d

commit_message:
tests/unit: Initialize core plugin in TestL3GwModeMixin

TestL3GwModeMixin can fail randomly because it doesn't initialize
core_plugin and can be run random core plugin depending on execution
order of tests. It also fails with core plugin uninitialized when it
is run without other tests.

This patch refactors the setup code of core plugin and apply it to the
related tests.
This patch reveled the same bug of test_metaplugin.py which is also
fixed by this patch.

Closes-bug: #1273259
Change-Id: I3c1d4d8b3d69262b89c7747daa8267bf2c8e7f6b

Problem with 'alive' field. if you try this command you obtain an
unexpected response:

$ neutron agent-list --field agent_type
'alive'

The problem is that the 'alive' field is not checked for instanciate

"}]
commit_message:
Unexpected response in agent-list command

Problem with 'alive' field. if you try this command you obtain an
unexpected response:

$ neutron agent-list --field agent_type
'alive'

The problem is that the 'alive' field is not checked for instanciate
before to check its value. Under the hood, there is a non catched
Keyerror exception converted to unicode.

Change-Id: I59b313494605f64c5588324d1153614b1c11920f
Closes-Bug: #1271948

commit_message:
ensure linuxbridge dependency is installed on RHEL

Package['neutron-plugin-linuxbridge'] is defined in
plugins/linuxbridge.pp but is missing in agents/linuxbridge.pp.

If agents::linuxbridge is used directly, the package is not defined.
This changes fixes the situation on RHEL.

The problem has already been fixed for OVS in
changeset Iedf8a607915f65b7a8cf7af99749b9b65cba7bd9

Change-Id: Ic4e15825e4f2d1f2ce2c34d2fdb01c8f6b19d491
(cherry picked from commit
9bb97fd444f28f797fc500331e9c52b660680e07)

subject: Fix tools/graduate.sh for work with directories
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-10 11:32:38.000000000', 'files': ['tools/graduate.sh'], 'message': "Fix tools/graduate.sh for work with directories

graduate.sh script works fine with files, but if we try create
new oslo library from existing directory, we get an
incorrect file structure.

For example if we run

 tools/graduate.sh foo openstack/common/foo/ tests/unit/test_foo/

We'll get file structure like

 oslo/foo/foo/file1.py

Added to graduate.sh `is directory` check to fix this issue.

Change-Id: Idd73288b12db54a44de14dbdef44fd8fd6617373
"}]
commit_message:
Fix tools/graduate.sh for work with directories

graduate.sh script works fine with files, but if we try create
new oslo library from existing directory, we get an
incorrect file structure.

For example if we run

 tools/graduate.sh foo openstack/common/foo/ tests/unit/test_foo/

We'll get file structure like

 oslo/foo/foo/file1.py

Added to graduate.sh `is directory` check to fix this issue.

Change-Id: Idd73288b12db54a44de14dbdef44fd8fd6617373

commit_message:
Add a Merge::Map feature.

We need to scatter gather in a few situations - determining rabbit
cluster membership, galera membership and configuring hosts for Nova
to permit live migration (which requires host->host communication).
This patch is a proof of concept for an eventual heat feature,
expressed in merge.py. The example given should work for actual use,
but I'll deliver that change separately.

Change-Id: I68e9b2471866810cc698ca3ea28ddf5bb1688d7b

subject: Stop using deprecated libvirt_type setting.
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-19 06:33:55.000000000', 'files': ['elements/nova/os-apply-config/etc/nova/nova.conf'], 'message': "Stop using deprecated libvirt_type setting.

Nova's libvirt driver now wants virt_type in the libvirt section.

I've made [libvirt] always be present because our current structure
cannot tell what to do when there are multiple libvirt options (which
my next patch adds). Refactoring of the heat metadata would permit
that - but that should be a separate pass.

Change-Id: Ie9e2a69c3fd51a8a17b44853b2608d95628aab2d
"}]
commit_message:
Stop using deprecated libvirt_type setting.

Nova's libvirt driver now wants virt_type in the libvirt section.

I've made [libvirt] always be present because our current structure
cannot tell what to do when there are multiple libvirt options (which
my next patch adds). Refactoring of the heat metadata would permit
that - but that should be a separate pass.

Change-Id: Ie9e2a69c3fd51a8a17b44853b2608d95628aab2d

commit_message:
Rename oslo.test to oslotest

The testing strategy for this library has changed, and so it
will not be installed via devstack like the other oslo libraries.
That means we don't want it in the oslo namespace package,
to avoid issues like bug 1277168.

Change-Id: I3ca1104663d0c89a351f4cc830414b41bb23fa29

commit_message:
Ensure return for db api functions

Functions in db/api.py should return whatever the implementation of
those functions return. This is important for qos_specs_update which
returns something for the sqlalchemy implementation, but for others as
well for future implementations.

Added 'return' for functions that were missing it.

Closes-Bug: #1272365

subject: Allow db fields configuration without doing the dbsync
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-20 15:03:33.000000000', 'files': ['spec/classes/ceilometer_db_spec.rb', 'manifests/db.pp'], 'message': "Allow db fields configuration without doing the dbsync

This commit allows one to configure the db fields without running the actual
dbsync command. It remains compliant with the current implementation, leaving
exec {'ceilometer-dbsync': in the catalog. One, now, can decide if it wants
the dbsync to take place or not.

This is useful when one picks mongodb as a backend and wants to use replicaset
This way it can scale horizontally and painlessly using the initSync feature
of mongodb. With this pattern one can add new member of the replica set
easily.

Change-Id: I8618bb385147176512fbda1540ba75ac95fccbf1
"}]
commit_message:
Allow db fields configuration without doing the dbsync

This commit allows one to configure the db fields without running the actual
dbsync command. It remains compliant with the current implementation, leaving
exec {'ceilometer-dbsync': in the catalog. One, now, can decide if it wants
the dbsync to take place or not.

This is useful when one picks mongodb as a backend and wants to use replicaset
This way it can scale horizontally and painlessly using the initSync feature
of mongodb. With this pattern one can add new member of the replica set
easily.

Change-Id: I8618bb385147176512fbda1540ba75ac95fccbf1

failure, and avoid waiting for something that can never happen.

subject: Move read/write handles in VMware drivers to OSLO
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-20 14:04:59.000000000', 'files': ['oslo/vmware/rw_handles.py', 'tests/test_rw_handles.py'], 'message': 'Move read/write handles in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes defining
read and write handles for image transfer between VMware servers and
image service into OSLO.

Change-Id: Idd5e0a3e13bb1e752ed577b63a012ca59c461bce
Implements: blueprint vmware-api
'}]
commit_message:
Move read/write handles in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes defining
read and write handles for image transfer between VMware servers and
image service into OSLO.

Change-Id: Idd5e0a3e13bb1e752ed577b63a012ca59c461bce
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

Switch to using the type checking decode_json

the decode_json helper that checks the root elements

commit_message:
Remove instruction setting ovs_use_veth to True

Remove instruction to set ovs_use_veth to True. Updated kernels shipped
to RDO/RHELOSP, and in RHEL/CentOS 6.5, mean that this is no longer
required. The updated kernels support network namespaces properly.

Change-Id: I6d34f924c1d93b6b7de2b0b7885755e48263a4d4

commit_message:
Fix DictOpt support in config sample generator

Class DictOpt was defined in oslo.config.cfg .
The config sample generator cannot recognize DictOpt type config options,
and will exit with exception when generating config sample files from codes
that contain DictOpt type options. This will result in unexpected output
of tools/config/generate_sample.sh and tools/config/check_uptodate.sh.
This problem is fixed by adding DictOpt support to config sample generator.

Change-Id: Ia360dbfae8446ddaa563e94f51900071e95cdf6d
Closes: bug #1276859

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-01-09 14:06:41.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/apiclient/exceptions.py'], 'message': 'Handle 300 status code in common HTTPClient

Common HTTPClient uses requests library for http communication, but
this library raise no exception if we get code 300 as response status.
On the other hand, some openstack clients (ceilometerclient,
glanceclient, heatclient, ironiccilent, tuskarclient) handles this
status code and raise a special exception in such case. So we should
provide a special exception for 300 status code in common apiclient.

Added required exception - MultipleChoices.

blueprint common-client-library-2

Change-Id: I991737dd4c2d8bdf8bbb5380f05d4cf2b3bcf953
'}]
commit_message:
Handle 300 status code in common HTTPClient

Common HTTPClient uses requests library for http communication, but
this library raise no exception if we get code 300 as response status.
On the other hand, some openstack clients (ceilometerclient,
glanceclient, heatclient, ironiccilent, tuskarclient) handles this
status code and raise a special exception in such case. So we should
provide a special exception for 300 status code in common apiclient.

Added required exception - MultipleChoices.

blueprint common-client-library-2

Change-Id: I991737dd4c2d8bdf8bbb5380f05d4cf2b3bcf953

commit_message:
Add test for raising errors in HTTPClient

Class `HTTPClient` doesn't have tests for raising errors.
This patch tests HTTPClient:
* when server returned status code #400 (Bad Request);
* when auth plugin does not return any token and endpoint.
* when client_request raises Unauthorized

Change-Id: Ic30db9fade2368c51db742d3809e84885b8e41b3

commit_message:
Modify assert statement when comparing with None

Replace assertEqual(None, *) with assertIsNone in glance's
tests to have more clear messages in case of failure.

Also, replace assertTrue(* is not None) with assertIsNotNone
for the same reason.

Change-Id: If41a71bd750057c7136b03bef94c04517092134c
Closes-Bug: #1280522

commit_message:
Add V3 api for pci support

All pci passthrough code is merged into nova, but the APIs are not supported.
This patch provides a resource: endpoint to show PCI information. This is a
part of PCI APIs, for more information see the blueprint.

Partially implement blueprint pci-api-support

subject: Improve StaticWeb 404 on web-listings/index
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-18 11:46:53.000000000', 'files': ['swift/common/middleware/staticweb.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_staticweb.py'], 'message': 'Improve StaticWeb 404 on web-listings/index

A common scenario is for users to make a container public via an ACL.
They can then use a browser to display the objects in the container.
Next, they enable StaticWeb with something such as
"X-Container-Meta-Web-Index:index.html" -- but then get confused
because they get 404 Not Found (when index.html does not exist).

For someone who understands what they are doing, this makes sense.
However, we've had several customer escalations because of this.
Usually, they are just playing with our GUI and have no intention
of using StaticWeb for real -- the 404 looks like something is
broken; not the correct response.

The solution is to provide a better error message. This message is only
shown when StaticWeb is refusing to give a listing -- other 404 situations
are not affected. Also, a custom 404 error page is not affected.

Change-Id: I3ba8c48e0ce148d8e91a1e0dc16a0d37a692a24e
'}]
commit_message:
Improve StaticWeb 404 on web-listings/index

A common scenario is for users to make a container public via an ACL.
They can then use a browser to display the objects in the container.
Next, they enable StaticWeb with something such as
"X-Container-Meta-Web-Index:index.html" -- but then get confused
because they get 404 Not Found (when index.html does not exist).

For someone who understands what they are doing, this makes sense.
However, we've had several customer escalations because of this.
Usually, they are just playing with our GUI and have no intention
of using StaticWeb for real -- the 404 looks like something is
broken; not the correct response.

The solution is to provide a better error message. This message is only
shown when StaticWeb is refusing to give a listing -- other 404 situations
are not affected. Also, a custom 404 error page is not affected.

Change-Id: I3ba8c48e0ce148d8e91a1e0dc16a0d37a692a24e

commit_message:
Glance all: Replace basestring by six for python3 compatability

The builtin basestring abstract type was removed in python3,
use str instead, we need to using six.string_types to replace
the basestring for py3 compatibility.

Change-Id: Icf709b3499ff7f1ea935045153eb9a5ecb4618ee

commit_message:
add output-list and output-show

This patch adds the "output-list" and "output-show" commands to heat.
The first prints a table of available outputs to stdout, and the second
prints a single output_value to stdout.

All outputs are serialized to JSON.

This patch includes tests for the new commands as well as updated
documentation.

Implements blueprint: stack-outputs-in-shell

Change-Id: Iaade16d043b2c42d14f642fde17419eaa07d0ab8
Closes-Bug: 1258622

commit_message:
vshield task manager: abort tasks in stop() on termination

This patch kills the manager thread, and aborts active tasks
rather than sending an exception to the manager thread and
have it do the abort on termination.

Unit tests involving vshield task manager might take longer
as a side effect of this patch.

Related-bug: #1282452

Change-Id: I9e9e41ce7e8969a2ea51bfce96b1303125a24308

The config sample generator supports plugins for libraries, but that
does not work for some applications. In particular, keystone has a
well-organized dictionary of options that the discovery code does
not recognize. This change allows an app to provide a function with a

commit_message:
Look for well-defined options function

The config sample generator supports plugins for libraries, but that
does not work for some applications. In particular, keystone has a
well-organized dictionary of options that the discovery code does
not recognize. This change allows an app to provide a function with a
well-defined name which will be discovered and used to retrieve option
definitions, just like the plugins.

Change-Id: Ie4d5ea8c474d961aeaf8d12538a4ac394c231400

existence.

subject: Nova baremetal: use mkfs/rsync instead of dd
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 2, 'name': 'Monty Taylor', 'email': 'mordred@inaugust.com', 'username': 'mordred'}, {'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 360, 'name': 'Dan Prince', 'email': 'dprince@redhat.com', 'username': 'dan-prince'}, {'_account_id': 475, 'name': 'Rick Harris', 'email': 'rick.harris@rackspace.com', 'username': 'rconradharris'}, {'_account_id': 4190, 'name': 'lifeless', 'email': 'robertc@robertcollins.net', 'username': 'lifeless'}, {'_account_id': 9008, 'name': 'VMware NSX CI', 'username': 'vmwareminesweeper', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9578, 'name': 'DB Datasets CI', 'email': 'turbo-hipster@lists.rcbops.com', 'username': 'turbo-hipster', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-02-17 18:02:59.000000000', 'files': ['etc/nova/rootwrap.d/baremetal-deploy-helper.filters', 'nova/cmd/baremetal_deploy_helper.py', 'nova/tests/virt/baremetal/test_nova_baremetal_deploy_helper.py'], 'message': "Nova baremetal: use mkfs/rsync instead of dd

The Nova baremetal-deploy-helper utility currently uses dd
to copy the root partition data from the compute host to
the instance being deployed.

With dd we blast out our pre-made filesystem to each disk
and then use resize2fs to grow it to the actual size of the root
partition on first boot.

This is causing some subtle file system problems and chicken/egg sorts
of issues with images:

1) It forces us know something about how large disk will be
when you build your images. By default ext4 file systems can
only be resized up to a certain amount (by a factor of around 1000 or so).
So if your file system is really large you could hit this limit
on first boot w/ resize2fs.

2) We currently have a hack around #1 above by setting the max-online-resize
option for mkfs.ext4 to something really large. By doing this today
we allow for root partitions up to 1PB (fairly large).

3) In general #2 works but we are hitting some intermittent resize2fs
issues: See, https://bugs.launchpad.net/diskimage-builder/+bug/1280709
Also #2 has a cost in that your file system layout and size aren't
ideal.

---------

In this patch we swap out dd and use mkfs directly on the root partition
and then use rsync to copy data. This allows us to avoid quirky
issues with ext4 resizing which really weren't intended to be used like
we are currently using them (resizing a 2G file system up to a 1PB
is not what the file system designers had in mind here)

In my tests the entire mkfs/rsync function is around 15-20 percent
faster than the old dd function as well.

Closes-bug: 1280709
Change-Id: Ia71f8bbb59637fd20e35db958e4fb92262e071bc
"}]
commit_message:
Nova baremetal: use mkfs/rsync instead of dd

The Nova baremetal-deploy-helper utility currently uses dd
to copy the root partition data from the compute host to
the instance being deployed.

With dd we blast out our pre-made filesystem to each disk
and then use resize2fs to grow it to the actual size of the root
partition on first boot.

This is causing some subtle file system problems and chicken/egg sorts
of issues with images:

1) It forces us know something about how large disk will be
when you build your images. By default ext4 file systems can
only be resized up to a certain amount (by a factor of around 1000 or so).
So if your file system is really large you could hit this limit
on first boot w/ resize2fs.

2) We currently have a hack around #1 above by setting the max-online-resize
option for mkfs.ext4 to something really large. By doing this today
we allow for root partitions up to 1PB (fairly large).

3) In general #2 works but we are hitting some intermittent resize2fs
issues: See, https://bugs.launchpad.net/diskimage-builder/+bug/1280709
Also #2 has a cost in that your file system layout and size aren't
ideal.

---------

In this patch we swap out dd and use mkfs directly on the root partition
and then use rsync to copy data. This allows us to avoid quirky
issues with ext4 resizing which really weren't intended to be used like
we are currently using them (resizing a 2G file system up to a 1PB
is not what the file system designers had in mind here)

In my tests the entire mkfs/rsync function is around 15-20 percent
faster than the old dd function as well.

Closes-bug: 1280709
Change-Id: Ia71f8bbb59637fd20e35db958e4fb92262e071bc

revisions:
[{'number': 29, 'created': '2014-02-18 14:25:32.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py', 'nova/virt/vmwareapi/error_util.py', 'nova/virt/vmwareapi/fake.py', 'nova/tests/virt/vmwareapi/test_driver_api.py'], 'message': 'VMware: prevent race for vmdk deletion

Prevent a race condition for the deletion of a file when there
is more than one process trying to erase the file.

In the application we can now handle the following specific exceptions:
 - CannotDeleteFile - the file cannot be deleted
 - FileFault - a file access exception
 - FileLocked - an attempt is made to lock a file that is
                already in use
 - FileNotFound - the specific file does not exist

Closes-bug: #1266580

commit_message:
VMware: prevent race for vmdk deletion

Prevent a race condition for the deletion of a file when there
is more than one process trying to erase the file.

In the application we can now handle the following specific exceptions:
 - CannotDeleteFile - the file cannot be deleted
 - FileFault - a file access exception
 - FileLocked - an attempt is made to lock a file that is
                already in use
 - FileNotFound - the specific file does not exist

Change-Id: I58e07b9e630c063f894cbbb138612a39e912acd5
Closes-bug: #1266580

commit_message:
VMware: raise more specific exceptions

In certain cases the exception handling for backend errors
would be handled too broadly. This patch elevates the backend exception
to the application so that it can treat specific errors.

In the application we can now handle the following specific exceptions:
 - FileAlreadyExists - for example when moving a directory to a directory
                       that already exists
 - InvalidProperty - for example when using neutron and opaque networks
                     are not supported
 - AlreadyExists - for example a port group already exists
 - NotAuthenticated - for example the operation is denied as because a
                      session is not established

Related-Bug: #1266579
Related-Bug: #1266580
Closes-bug: #1276539

Co-authored-by: Matthew Booth <mbooth@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I0873f570d97345208c8d9b5bcbb5a980a7a58f9d

commit_message:
Emit message which merged user-supplied argument in log_handler

When using PublishErrorsHandler, it will missing user-supplied arguments.
For example, do LOG.info("blabla %s", "foo"), the payload only contains
"blabla %s", but we expect it like "blabla foo". This patch fix it.

Change-Id: I91289cc4a60f5dab89bca852e6f52b4b83831e47
Closes-bug: #1278291

commit_message:
Skip __pycache__ in maintainers check

When tox runs, tools/check_maintainers.py fails with an error
``Directory __pycache__ not found in MAINTAINERS``

This happens, because unittest on py33 was merged to master, and
python 3 stores bytecode in the __pycache__ folder. So we should
not check an entry for this folder in MAINTAINERS file.

Change-Id: I3f311f37262739e50a59164e204d8ff806f5f408

commit_message:
update.py fails silently if module is not found

update.py can be used to copy individual modules into OpenStack components by
using the --modules switch and providing a module name. However, if this module
is not found is oslo, the user is not informed that the copy failed. Print a
message in this case, and provide the path to the file that the script tried
to copy.

Change-Id: I6f811cd9a412d83a4d83f29c8f8398ca0503f7f4
Closes-Bug: #1274647

commit_message:
Refactor dhcp checker to use pcap

Scapy packet filtering is slow and blocking.
Pcap filtering can be used in same thread,
this allows us to use higher timeout for dhcp offer waiting

Setup proper logger for dhcp_checker app.
ERROR level logs will be redirected to stderr
DEBUG level to /var/log/dhcp_checker.log

Change-Id: I7d9a0f1b8e3082637bc2474302fc0f7c17e0adb8
Closes-Bug: #1247284

commit_message:
VMware: factor out management of controller keys and unit numbers

This patch encapsulates the allocation of controller key and unit
number for a new virtual disk/CDROM into utility function.
This way high-level methods like spawn, rescue, etc. don't have
to deal with implementation details like the above and the
algorithm for allocating controller_key and unit_number is
clearly defined and can be easily reused.

Change-Id: Ia6d5db5d5c5fa25f680eae82892dcb9b2be864fa
Closes-Bug: #1259981

commit_message:
Refactor timestamp existence validation in V2 API

There was a bug in AlarmThresholdRule in v2.py, the timestamp_keys
were defined with a missing comma:
['timestamp', 'start', 'start_timestamp' 'end', 'end_timestamp'].

The validation, if the timestamp field is used or not, was unclear
in the current implementation. A new parameter, 'timestamp_is_valid',
was added to the validation functions to show, if the timestamp is
allowed to use or not in the validated query.

Fixes bug 1280975

Change-Id: I17889b2199484166b22055578553fe30e4135d4d

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-17 13:26:27.000000000', 'files': ['tests/unit/vmware/test_api.py', 'openstack/common/vmware/exceptions.py', 'openstack/common/vmware/vim.py', 'openstack/common/vmware/api.py', 'tests/unit/vmware/test_vim.py'], 'message': 'VMware: raise more specific exceptions

In certain cases the exception handling for backend errors
would be handled too broadly. This patch elevates the backend exception
to the application so that it can treat specific errors.

In the application we can now handle the following specific exceptions:
- FileAlreadyExists - for example when moving a directory to a directory
that already exists
- InvalidProperty - for example when using neutron and opaque networks
are not supported

- NotAuthenticated - for example the operation is denied as because a
session is not established
- CannotDeleteFile - the file cannot be deleted
- FileFault - a file access exception
- FileLocked - an attempt is made to lock a file that is
already in use
- FileNotFound - the specific file does not exist

Change-Id: I81059e47cab30fea4ca9374f38d29fd1d9fdacf7
'}]
commit_message:
VMware: raise more specific exceptions

In certain cases the exception handling for backend errors
would be handled too broadly. This patch elevates the backend exception
to the application so that it can treat specific errors.

In the application we can now handle the following specific exceptions:
- FileAlreadyExists - for example when moving a directory to a directory
that already exists
- InvalidProperty - for example when using neutron and opaque networks
are not supported
- AlreadyExists - for example a port group already exists
- NotAuthenticated - for example the operation is denied as because a
session is not established
- CannotDeleteFile - the file cannot be deleted
- FileFault - a file access exception
- FileLocked - an attempt is made to lock a file that is
already in use
- FileNotFound - the specific file does not exist

Change-Id: I81059e47cab30fea4ca9374f38d29fd1d9fdacf7

commit_message:
Move API invocation code in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes in
VMware drivers for session and API call management calls into OSLO.

The api module in this change contains classes to invoke VIM APIs.
It supports automatic session re-establishment and retry of API
invocations in case of connection problems or server API call overload.

Change-Id: I74e2be632631f83a97e26c03e33f1d9ae7632e27
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the classes in
VMware drivers for making VIM API SOAP calls into OSLO.

We removed this a while ago, but unfortunately Nova, Ironic and
probably other projects still rely on this feature to prevent import
cycles and postpone initialization of DB backend to the moment when
oslo.config has already parsed the config files (the errors were
hidden when we tested the original commit by the fact that we had

This is needed in order to make transitioning of existing projects

commit_message:
Restore the ability to load the DB backend lazily

We removed this a while ago, but unfortunately Nova, Ironic and
probably other projects still rely on this feature to prevent import
cycles and postpone initialization of DB backend to the moment when
oslo.config has already parsed the config files (the errors were
hidden when we tested the original commit by the fact that we had
lazy loading of engines in oslo.db code).

This is needed in order to make transitioning of existing projects
to oslo.db as smooth as possible.

Blueprint: oslo-db-lib

Change-Id: I9fe09c132c716345f1cef240483b023e850d4989

commit_message:
Linux bridge naming convention emphasized

The value for the flat_network_bridge setting can be modified from
the default br100. I added a line emphasizing that any new value
must adhere to the linux bridge naming conventions.

for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also

commit_message:
Move utility methods in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves the utility methods
for inventory traversal spec creation, managed object property retrieval
etc. defined in various drivers into OSLO.

Change-Id: Ibdd80188ffb0936468545ceec86b67162a111fff
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

[{'number': 7, 'created': '2014-02-18 16:57:23.000000000', 'files': ['recipes/dhcp_agent.rb'], 'message': 'Wait for dnsmasq to become available

Fixes: bug 1280214

When we install dnsmasq, it takes a few seconds to start up, during
which time dns resolution on the system is unavailable.  If we carry on
with the chef run during this time, subsequent steps (eg package

before moving on

'}]
commit_message:
Wait for dnsmasq to become available

Fixes: bug 1280214

When we install dnsmasq, it takes a few seconds to start up, during
which time dns resolution on the system is unavailable.  If we carry on
with the chef run during this time, subsequent steps (eg package
installations) will fail due to transient errors with name resolution.

This patch introduces a small loop to ensure we have working dns resolution
before moving on

Change-Id: Ia508a7243554bca64c0451d99086ae596ec9e462

ensure openvswitch kernel module is reloaded properly

sometimes the openvswitch kernel module does not get reloaded properly when
openvswitch-datapath-dkms recompiles it.  This ensures that it does by
calling the force-reload-kmod script

commit_message:
Change platform? check in template

Rendering this template currently returns a
Chef::Mixin::Template::TemplateError error on the platform? method.  We
could change the method to node.platform? however this then triggers an
FC028 error.

Note that this issue is only encountered when
node[openstack][block-storage][volume][create_volume_group] set to
true.

Change-Id: I4d5ce97762c6b82bbf10e8194c482049eb3a6620
Closes-Bug: #1280285

commit_message:
make dnsmasq compile optional

Some users wont want to compile source, and instead choose
to build or otherwise install a package for dnsmasq on precise
This does not change the default behavior, just provides a short circuit
mechanism for folks who don't want to have these recipes build from
source

Change-Id: I85ee904f2bc47dc352b13e2c6f35e14e2084b5d2

subject: Use disk_bus when guessing the device name for vol
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-19 20:18:34.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/blockinfo.py', 'nova/tests/virt/libvirt/test_libvirt_blockinfo.py'], 'message': "Use disk_bus when guessing the device name for vol

Even though the disk bus could be set through hw_disk_bus property,
the libvirt driver didn't guess the proper bus and device name for the
root volume and expected it to be defined in the BDM.

With this patch, we consider the predefined disk_bus when going to guess
the volume device name and bus instead of just relying on the one
defined in the BDM.

Change-Id: Ic6434ee2b29dc20126ec3b470d7340a0f8bf62e9
Closes-Bug: 1281989
"}]
commit_message:
Use disk_bus when guessing the device name for vol

Even though the disk bus could be set through hw_disk_bus property,
the libvirt driver didn't guess the proper bus and device name for the
root volume and expected it to be defined in the BDM.

With this patch, we consider the predefined disk_bus when going to guess
the volume device name and bus instead of just relying on the one
defined in the BDM.

Change-Id: Ic6434ee2b29dc20126ec3b470d7340a0f8bf62e9
Closes-Bug: 1281989

commit_message:
Changing to qpid does not set qpid attributes

The case statement needs to check the node's service_type, not the
default.  Checking the default will always result in the rabbitmq
attributes being set.

subject: Fix issue with new python-keystoneclient
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-20 11:16:59.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'climate/utils/openstack/keystone.py'], 'message': 'Fix issue with new python-keystoneclient

As new python-keystoneclient 0.6.0 was released, change
https://review.openstack.org/61247 was merged to it. This commit
changed work with keystoneclient adding session to request
processing from the very beginning, that caused empty self.auth
for this session. In fact that led to no auth-token header passed
to Keystone and unauthorised exception from it.

Change-Id: I67baecacde6f9c94152cd34aae03ba59a0a7a580
Closes-Bug: #1281487
'}]
commit_message:
Fix issue with new python-keystoneclient

As new python-keystoneclient 0.6.0 was released, change
https://review.openstack.org/61247 was merged to it. This commit
changed work with keystoneclient adding session to request
processing from the very beginning, that caused empty self.auth
for this session. In fact that led to no auth-token header passed
to Keystone and unauthorised exception from it.

Change-Id: I67baecacde6f9c94152cd34aae03ba59a0a7a580
Closes-Bug: #1281487

commit_message:
Refactor get_iscsi_initiator to a common location

Refactor get_iscsi_initiator to a common location so that other
drivers can use it, without reaching into virt/libvirt. This patch
updates the current baremetal volume driver to the new shared location.

commit_message:
Message-oriented worker-based flow with kombu

* Implemented Worker to be started on remote host for
  handling tasks request.
* Implemented WorkerTaskExecutor that proxies tasks
  requests to remote workers.
* Implemented Proxy that is used for consuming and
  publishing messages by Worker and Executor.
* Added worker-based engine and worker task executor.
* Added kombu dependency to requirements.
* Added worker-based flow example.
* Added unit-tests for worker-based flow components.

Implements: blueprint worker-based-engine
Change-Id: I8c6859ba4a1a56c2592e3d67cdfb8968b13ee99c

commit_message:
openSUSE package install support for neutron

On openSUSE, the user is openstack-neutron, not "neutron".
Prefer that user if available. Install the dhcp-agent
explicitely, since it doesn't come in via transitive
dependencies on openSUSE.

Remove some of the existing install hooks for openSUSE,
they're not needed there.

Change-Id: I63c994c101d68f36b32e31dfe084a88a17fe71bc

commit_message:
Nova package install support (openSUSE)

commit_message:
Ensure that exception raised in neutron are handled correctly

We are now logging exceptions so we need to use save_and_reraise.

The patch set has also added log messages for exceptions that were
raised. This will be very helpful for debugging and troubleshooting.
This is done in the following cases:
 - unable to access a port when validating networks
 - unable to find a requested floating ip

Change-Id: I946126c2fb5aa229f917f8cb36ecb23aab528e14

Add a parameter in tempest.conf "full_clean_stack" to

of a stress test run.

This is mandatory to use stress tests in a multi-user

Change-Id: I42dc9592617aeeca9660f670940ecbf50b6108ab
Closes-Bug: #1273254

commit_message:
cleanUp() removing all test resources as an admin

Add a parameter in tempest.conf "full_clean_stack" to
allow/prevent the use of cleanup() method at the end
of a stress test run.

This is mandatory to use stress tests in a multi-user
environment since the actual cleanup() is designed to
remove every object of every tenant (and thus will
impact other users on the same openstack)

Change-Id: I42dc9592617aeeca9660f670940ecbf50b6108ab
Closes-Bug: #1273254

commit_message:
Refactor timestamp existence validation in V2 API

There was a bug in AlarmThresholdRule in v2.py, the timestamp_keys
were defined with a missing comma:
['timestamp', 'start', 'start_timestamp' 'end', 'end_timestamp'].

The validation, if the timestamp field is used or not, was unclear
in the current implementation. A new parameter, 'timestamp_is_valid',
was added to the validation functions to show, if the timestamp is
allowed to use or not in the validated query.

Fixes bug 1280975

Change-Id: I2aaef54354926f9afe3bb1d4fae8f8aa0ae600ab

commit_message:
HP LeftHand Backend assisted volume migrate

This patch implements volume migrate using native LeftHand APIs.

Limitations:
1. Same LeftHand backend
2. Volume cannot be attached
3. Volumes with snapshots cannot be migrated
4. Source and Destination clusters must be in the same management group
5. Volume re-type not supported

Change-Id: I503d5a10ee59db14130c676a5c3a07abf9a2b7af
Implements: blueprint native-lefthand-volume-migrate

commit_message:
Add ssh console to anaconda and preseed

Adds ssh console to CentOS and Ubuntu nodes during provisioning.
SSH is accessible from Fuel master node via Admin network IPs with
Fuel root RSA ssh key. Password authentication is not available.

Anaconda/Debian-installer stop commands have been removed from the
login profiles. Orchestrator should execute something like the
following in order to pause provisioning on the node:

- CentOS/RH: "killall -STOP anaconda"
- Ubuntu: "killall -STOP debootstrap dpkg"

Change-Id: Ic34b7e6f154c084bd03c29cc5ce1d22edfc165ad
Closes-Bug: #1277447

commit_message:
Fix recursive_keypairs output

recursive_keypairs has 'separator' argument. This method is recursive
and a problem is that 'separator' argument is applied only in first
iteration of the method.

Besides, this method is used in flatten_metadata in API implementation.
That's why it is needed not to change output from recursive_keypairs in flatten_metadata.

So the path has a goal to fix incorrect recursive_keypairs impementation but
not to change output of flatten_matadata in API

Fixes bug 1268628

Change-Id: Ic9829342c47325c1df7b81dc4148c08a13e0d067

commit_message:
Print exceptions from scenarios only in case of debug

Exceptions are standard way to stop exectuion of one scenario iteration
so we shouldn't print them to end user, because it is "OK" that there are
exceptions specially in case of big load

Print ITER START/END and result of scenario loop (success/error)

Change-Id: I32a69b5b274097b5b06479a48f22ea8633d5cadd
Closes-bug: #1282088

commit_message:
Disallow create port if network is not shared

Admin user is able to create port whose tenant is different from the
owner network even the network is not shared. It isn't intended.

Change-Id: Iae9ca8da6f78607ecfd4ff797c18087b7019b8e1
Closes-Bug: #1279751

subject: Add support for location parameters in v2 commands
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-08 08:28:48.000000000', 'files': ['tests/v2/test_images.py', 'glanceclient/v2/images.py', 'glanceclient/v2/shell.py', 'tests/v2/test_shell_v2.py'], 'message': 'Add support for location parameters in v2 commands

Currently glanceclient's v2 commands don't support modification
operations on an image's location attribute - the argparse specification
for the location attribute of the image-update command causes the image
id argument to be included in list of locations and so the command
parsing fails (because it causes the image id to appear to be missing).

Furthermore even if the 'locations' argument were to be accepted by
argparse (e.g. by changing the argument specs and using --id to specify
the image id) the command would still fail because the arguments are
passed directly to the schema which expects the value of the 'locations'
argument to be a valid dictionary (there is nobody to convert the
argument string to a python dictionary that the schema expects).

This commit overrides the default 'locations' parameter definition
(which is inferred from the image schema) and instead provides
(simplified) operations on 'locations' via a set of parameters:

    *) Instead of allowing multiple locations to be added on the command
       line at most one location can be added per invocation on the
       command line using the '--location' option.

    *) The metadata for the location being added can be optionally
       specified using the '--metadata' option.

    *) An existing location can be removed using the '--remove-location'
       option. This option can be used multiple times in one invocation
       to remove multiple locations.

    *) The '--location' option can also be invoked to modify the
       metadata for an existing url. However, due to the way the glance
       server is implemented, one cannot modify only one url in the
       location list - the entire 'locations' attribute must be first
       cleared and then set to the new value.

       This will result in two requests - one to clear the existing set
       of locations and the second to set it to the new value. The
       update operation is therefore NOT atomic. This needs to be fixed
       once the server provides a (true) location update API.

The v2 'image' and 'shell' related tests have also been supplemented.

Note that in order to use these options the server must be first
configured to expose location related info to the clients (i.e.
'show_multiple_locations' must be set to 'True").

Change-Id: Ibe85b192b2f40bb1b81bf6136897ded2bfc363ff
Closes-bug: #1271452
'}]
commit_message:
Add support for location parameters in v2 commands

Currently glanceclient's v2 commands don't support modification
operations on an image's location attribute - the argparse specification
for the location attribute of the image-update command causes the image
id argument to be included in list of locations and so the command
parsing fails (because it causes the image id to appear to be missing).

Furthermore even if the 'locations' argument were to be accepted by
argparse (e.g. by changing the argument specs and using --id to specify
the image id) the command would still fail because the arguments are
passed directly to the schema which expects the value of the 'locations'
argument to be a valid dictionary (there is nobody to convert the
argument string to a python dictionary that the schema expects).

This commit overrides the default 'locations' parameter definition
(which is inferred from the image schema) and instead provides
(simplified) operations on 'locations' via a set of parameters:

    *) Instead of allowing multiple locations to be added on the command
       line at most one location can be added per invocation on the
       command line using the '--location' option.

    *) The metadata for the location being added can be optionally
       specified using the '--metadata' option.

    *) An existing location can be removed using the '--remove-location'
       option. This option can be used multiple times in one invocation
       to remove multiple locations.

    *) The '--location' option can also be invoked to modify the
       metadata for an existing url. However, due to the way the glance
       server is implemented, one cannot modify only one url in the
       location list - the entire 'locations' attribute must be first
       cleared and then set to the new value.

       This will result in two requests - one to clear the existing set
       of locations and the second to set it to the new value. The
       update operation is therefore NOT atomic. This needs to be fixed
       once the server provides a (true) location update API.

The v2 'image' and 'shell' related tests have also been supplemented.

Note that in order to use these options the server must be first
configured to expose location related info to the clients (i.e.
'show_multiple_locations' must be set to 'True").

Change-Id: Ibe85b192b2f40bb1b81bf6136897ded2bfc363ff
Closes-bug: #1271452

subject: Fix wrong quota reservation in revert resize
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-11 08:24:51.000000000', 'files': ['nova/compute/manager.py', 'nova/compute/api.py'], 'message': "Fix wrong quota reservation in revert resize

it is that, if the resized instance is reverted through admin user,
then the project_id and user_id in context are all admin's, which
result in reservations in DB are also have wrong project_id and
user_id, when these reservations are committed, the quotas usage of
the instance's project/user will become wrong eventually.

This change fixes the above bug by using the instance's project_id
and user_id instead of the context's, then the reservations will
be committed to correct project/user.

Closes-bug: #1278695

Change-Id: Idde6222609c03a97e8cb0c0ba418574ef1991a0e
"}]
commit_message:
Fix wrong quota reservation in revert resize

it is that, if the resized instance is reverted through admin user,
then the project_id and user_id in context are all admin's, which
result in reservations in DB are also have wrong project_id and
user_id, when these reservations are committed, the quotas usage of
the instance's project/user will become wrong eventually.

This change fixes the above bug by using the instance's project_id
and user_id instead of the context's, then the reservations will
be committed to correct project/user.

Closes-bug: #1278695

Change-Id: Idde6222609c03a97e8cb0c0ba418574ef1991a0e

L3 service integration with service framework

commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Ensure we are not exhausting the sqlalchemy pool""

This reverts commit d1fe25ad6a3d9d96c73100df0317c5b2ed54af07.

Unfortunately not having Eventlet on socket makes the collector blocked
entirely, as oslo.rpc depends on Eventlet.

Restore this patch before restoring eventlet on socket.

commit_message:
Change pagination related methods of mongodb and db2

Put all parameters for paginate query in one class,
named pagination, includes limit, primary_sort_dir,
marker_value, sort_keys and sort_dirs.
And request a single marker value passed from users and it should be
specific enough to identify only one object in the database.
Get_resource uses aggregation and not support pagination for now.
Support multiple sort keys and sort directions combination.

Changes also made to db2 to support multiple sort directions while
generate sort_instruction.

It is part of bp/paginate-db-search.

Implements blueprint paginate-db-search

Change-Id: I08f8d73254ddcd9ce1522e343193d37f6ea6daa7

commit_message:
Use working default settings for ec2 test

Devstack configures the path with cirros-0.3.1, but does not
configures the manifest file names with the new version, it leads
to the ec2 test cases are autoskiped.

It should be improved on devstack side as well, but looks like there are
other issues which needs to be addressed, but anyway the default tempest
config should be closer, to the actually used one.

commit_message:
Dynamic pipelines for server configuration

This patch allows admins of systems who use software that
generates/controls swift config files to add items to an existing swift
configuration that uses the conf.d-style without intruding on the
managing system.  This is done by adding a new config file in the
config.d directory with a filter section declared in it, and explicitly
declaring the ordering dependencies of that filter with other items in
the pipeline.

Other features:

Dynamic pipelines rendered under conf.d only
Added config.d documentation to proxy-server man page

Change-Id: Id40841f8b007a1b3779704c4f43792c7ecc79dff

commit_message:
Print docker-registry log upon failure

Various bugs have been spotted in running
the docker registry, both by users and in
CI. It will be easier to debug, especially for CI,
if the failure were visible in logs.

Upon a failed lauch of the docker-registry,
we'll now print the registry's log to STDOUT.

fixes bug #1274984

Change-Id: I5c06163085059223b79c5ed8ab2036031a6fd340

commit_message:
Parse JSON in ovs_lib.get_vif_port_by_id

This patch replaces regex matching of text output with parsing
of JSON output in ovs_lib.get_vif_port_by_id.
This makes the code more reliable as subtle, possibly even
cosmetic, changes in ovs-vsctl output format could cause the
regular expression match to fail.

Also, this makes the code consistent with ovs_lib.get_vif_port_set
which already uses JSON output.

Finally this patch slightly changes the behaviour of
ovs_lib.get_vif_port_by_id returning None if elements such as
mac address or ofport were not available.

Change-Id: Ia985a130739c72b5b88414a79b2c6083ca6a0a00
Closes-Bug: #1280827

commit_message:
Swiftclient should switch to using bufferedhttp

Swiftclient should switch to using bufferedhttp like in swift which
makes up for missing features in traditional httplib, for eg)
buffering http headers, support for 'Expect: 100-continue' etc.
This patch pulls in the bufferedhttp from swift.

Related to bp use-bufferedhttp-in-swiftclient
Change-Id: I65f0b0f62f5d89bc8dd24b1260531e1f1d3555c8

subject: Fix GETs of SLOs and DLOs with If-Modified-Since
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-14 00:05:17.000000000', 'files': ['swift/common/utils.py', 'swift/common/middleware/slo.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_slo.py', 'test/unit/common/middleware/test_dlo.py', 'swift/common/middleware/dlo.py'], 'message': "Fix GETs of SLOs and DLOs with If-Modified-Since

Both SLO and DLO will raise errors if they try to fetch a segment and
get a non-2xx response. Well, if the client passed in an
If-Modified-Since or If-Unmodified-Since header, that'd get passed
along for all the segment requests, and if that happened to result in
a 304, then it's error time.

Now SLO and DLO strip those headers off for submanifest requests
(SLO), container listing requests (DLO), and segment requests (both).

Change-Id: I0432bbe8404159dab1485e57eaf9e111de486baa
Closes-Bug: 1280022
Closes-Bug: 1280028
"}]
commit_message:
Fix GETs of SLOs and DLOs with If-Modified-Since

Both SLO and DLO will raise errors if they try to fetch a segment and
get a non-2xx response. Well, if the client passed in an
If-Modified-Since or If-Unmodified-Since header, that'd get passed
along for all the segment requests, and if that happened to result in
a 304, then it's error time.

Now SLO and DLO strip those headers off for submanifest requests
(SLO), container listing requests (DLO), and segment requests (both).

Change-Id: I0432bbe8404159dab1485e57eaf9e111de486baa
Closes-Bug: 1280022
Closes-Bug: 1280028

required and posts a link to the documentation section.

commit_message:
Convert Token Memcache backend to new KeyValueStore Impl

This patchset converts the memcache backend for tokens to the new
KeyValueStore implementation.  This implementation provides basic
configuration choices for utilizing memcache as a token backend.

The test_backend_memcache test suite has been removed, as there is
no extra functionality added on top of the KeyValueStore base
besides the basic configuration choices.  The test_backend_memcache
test suite was only used for testing token memcache backend.  The
important unicode tests have been moved into the base token test
suite and should now validate against all token backends.

Closes-Bug: #1260080
bp: dogpile-kvs-backends
Change-Id: I8f0bca409a6393176e77f7a27ba15959756da06f

The error message when using an invalid os-compute-api-version is
created by joining all the available versions without space.
This patch will add ', ' between versions.

Ex: nova --os-compute-api-version v3 list
ERROR: Invalid client version 'v3'. must be one of: 321.1

ERROR: Invalid client version 'v3'. must be one of: 3, 2, 1.1

commit_message:
Test query-string for list actions with filter arguments

httpretty.register_uri only matches the path, not the query
string, so the test_list will pass even if the query string
passed by the manager doesn't match that passed as part of
expected_path.

So add a test for the query component of all list requests,
and a way to override the expected query, which is needed in
the trusts list filter tests where the query string doesn't
exactly match the kwargs passed to the client API.

Change-Id: I290b73bbbdac88487c225063fd3775ab7dd8bb89

commit_message:
Fix assignment KVS backend to not use identity

The assignment KVS backend was using the identity API. This change
makes it so that the KVS backend does not use the identity API.

The assignment KVS backend was using the identity API to:

a) Store the user's projects.

The user's projects were also kept in the metadata. So the KVS
backend was changed to use the metadata rather than the user data.

a) Determine if the ID in the metadata was for a user or group.

The metadata for users and groups was split into separate keys.
Metadata for users is now prefixed with `metadata_user-` and
`metadata-groups-` is used for groups.

commit_message:
Implement mechanism to provide non-expiring keys in KVS

This patchset implements the ability to define non-expiring keys
for dogpile.cache backends. The non-expiring keys are relevant
in the case of drivers that can automatically remove keys after
a given time (e.g. memcache). This new non-expiring-key
functionality is currently only implemented for the provided
memcached backend.

bp: dogpile-kvs-backends
Change-Id: I7e25e0049e5b8697c5cb67272b660519c3c3305e

commit_message:
str2dict support commas within quotes

neutronclient.common.str2dict split string 'key1=value1,key2=value2' by comma
and doesn't consider commas within quotes, so the client cann't support any
value itself contains commas like 'key1=value1,key2="part1,part2"'.

subject: Sync log.py from oslo
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-20 00:37:24.000000000', 'files': ['etc/keystone.conf.sample', 'keystone/openstack/common/log.py'], 'message': 'Sync log.py from oslo

This change syncs log.py from oslo-incubator with commit
79e8a9a08daf563aa8a8d9280c9a6a27dcafc8f2

To honor RFC5424 add use_syslog_rfc_format config option
(default False, would be deprecated in J after existing
syslog format deprecation) which adds APP-NAME to syslog message
before MSG part to reflect application or service name.
Usable only with use_syslog, otherwise ignored.

During J, the default logging format for syslog should be changed
to always provide APP-NAME, thus use_syslog_rfc_format could be
deprecated in J as well.

DocImpact

Closes-bug: 904307

Change-Id: Ia704e0735a38f0e9f6ad7a2d7c827c21e6637a31
'}]
commit_message:
Sync log.py from oslo

This change syncs log.py from oslo-incubator with commit
79e8a9a08daf563aa8a8d9280c9a6a27dcafc8f2

To honor RFC5424 add use_syslog_rfc_format config option
(default False, would be deprecated in J after existing
syslog format deprecation) which adds APP-NAME to syslog message
before MSG part to reflect application or service name.
Usable only with use_syslog, otherwise ignored.

During J, the default logging format for syslog should be changed
to always provide APP-NAME, thus use_syslog_rfc_format could be
deprecated in J as well.

DocImpact

Closes-bug: 904307

Change-Id: Ia704e0735a38f0e9f6ad7a2d7c827c21e6637a31

subject: Make max-online-resize an option.
revisions:
[{'number': 7, 'created': '2014-02-19 13:38:28.000000000', 'files': ['bin/disk-image-create'], 'message': "Make max-online-resize an option.

In fb246a02eb2ed330d3cc37f5795b3ed026aabe07 we introduced an
ext4 option to allow root filesystems to be resized up to 1PB.
This appears to cause an ext4 resize2fs bug in some images.

When the issue occurs an image will hit a kernel bug when
cloud-init runs the resize2fs command during first boot:

  kernel BUG at fs/ext4/resize.c:409!

In this commit we add a new option for max-online-resize
which can be used if a really large root partition is
desirable.

The root cause of all this is really a design problem in
DIB/TripleO at the moment in that we shouldn't have to worry about the
max size of the root file system when creating our images.  Ideally we'd
just mkfs on the root file system itself. Much more efficient,
avoids this problem altogether...

I think the best thing to do today to avoid this is make setting
max-online-resize an option in DIB. This will allow us to stick
to the (well tested) ext4 defaults for most cases, and if someone has
need for a large root filesystem they can easily bump the setting. This
may be temporary until we either fix the design... or the ext4 fix is
released.

Change-Id: I371f62555d2753cec48790c8fd811c4342af925c
Closes-bug: #1280709
"}]
commit_message:
Make max-online-resize an option.

In fb246a02eb2ed330d3cc37f5795b3ed026aabe07 we introduced an
ext4 option to allow root filesystems to be resized up to 1PB.
This appears to cause an ext4 resize2fs bug in some images.

When the issue occurs an image will hit a kernel bug when
cloud-init runs the resize2fs command during first boot:

  kernel BUG at fs/ext4/resize.c:409!

In this commit we add a new option for max-online-resize
which can be used if a really large root partition is
desirable.

The root cause of all this is really a design problem in
DIB/TripleO at the moment in that we shouldn't have to worry about the
max size of the root file system when creating our images.  Ideally we'd
just mkfs on the root file system itself. Much more efficient,
avoids this problem altogether...

I think the best thing to do today to avoid this is make setting
max-online-resize an option in DIB. This will allow us to stick
to the (well tested) ext4 defaults for most cases, and if someone has
need for a large root filesystem they can easily bump the setting. This
may be temporary until we either fix the design... or the ext4 fix is
released.

Change-Id: I371f62555d2753cec48790c8fd811c4342af925c
Closes-bug: #1280709

commit_message:
Don't lose AttributeError in API Wrappers

Instead of (implicitly) catching the AttributeError, and later
creating and raising a new one, we just re-raise the original
exception. This way all the information from the original is
retained, including the name of the actual object on which it
happened.

Change-Id: Idc0c5a8ed5dfca6a8724e393c220baf9960564ed
Closes-bug: #1274097

commit_message:
Rationalize the Assignment Grant Tables

Currently there are four different tables in the assignment sql
backend, one for each type of grant.  This leads to significantly
more complex code.

This patch rationalizes these four tables into a single Assignment
table, with the minimal of rework to calling functions of the
sql backend.  A subsequent patch will improve efficiency of the
calling code by taking advantage of a single Assignment table.

Blueprint: role-assignments-unified-sql

Change-Id: I7e604d718b29ad28b4d59458c7a528c01ff9804d

subject: Fix request id log messages
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-14 00:39:22.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/common/rest_client.py'], 'message': "Fix request id log messages

Previously when logging request ids tempest would incorrectly print
which service the request id came from. This was based on the faulty
assumption that x-compute-request-id was only returned by nova. It's
returned by both nova v2 and cinder. Also originally
x-openstack-request-id was only used by glance but other projects have
adopted it as well. Moving forward all the services will converge on
using that header. This commit just updates the log messages to make

header.

Change-Id: Idd0514794768840c2c9911ad189552cf455ea849
"}]
commit_message:
Fix request id log messages

Previously when logging request ids tempest would incorrectly print
which service the request id came from. This was based on the faulty
assumption that x-compute-request-id was only returned by nova. It's
returned by both nova v2 and cinder. Also originally
x-openstack-request-id was only used by glance but other projects have
adopted it as well. Moving forward all the services will converge on
using that header. This commit just updates the log messages to make
what is written to the log consistent with the current state of the
header.

Change-Id: Idd0514794768840c2c9911ad189552cf455ea849

commit_message:
Always pass 'modal' context variable to workflow template

Workflow templates rely on 'modal' context variable to be true for
modal dialogs. Still, when rendering from WorkflowView,
this variable is missing. This causes e.g. absent cancel and close
buttons in flavor creating dialog (and also affects Tuskar UI).

Change-Id: I76b1f0b97c14280db7cb880651e663147103438f
Closes-Bug: #1273874

commit_message:
MetricsWeigher: Added support of unavailable metrics

This patch added the support of unavailable metrics in the metric
weigher. Based on the configuration, if an unavailable metric is met,
the metric weigher might either throw an exception, or return an
configurable weight value.

This is part of the blueprint utilization-aware-scheduling.

DocImpact: Added support of unavailable metrics. 2 new config options
are added, 1) 'required' is a boolean option indicating whether all
the metrics set by 'weight_setting' are needed to be available when
calculating the weight. 2) 'weight_of_unavailable' is a float option
specifying the value to be returned if the metrics is unavailable. See
etc/nova/nova.conf.sample for details.

Change-Id: Icb951605aae28487b00a12d172a3ac4dafda2cdb

commit_message:
Prepare for enabling H302 rule (api/object_storage)

We can use H302 rule but ignore it now. This commit prepares for
enabling H302 rule. But this commit modifies tempest/api/object_storage
only and excludes some violations[1] because if we fix all of them at
one time, it's hard to merge this commit.

[1]
 tempest.test.attr

Horizon can provide GUI support for Neutron's LBaaS, FWaaS, VPNaas,

	spec/classes/horizon_init_spec.rb

Change-Id: Ibfa75a83a88d9bb26d65c026c7f913e000bce13f

(cherry picked from commit e2c0e7543a3e73013101fc34567a1850367538b1)
