commit_message:
Parameterize OPENSTACK_NEUTRON_NETWORK settings

Horizon can provide GUI support for Neutron's LBaaS, FWaaS, VPNaas,
and other services. However the settings to enable these is currently
hardcoded in the local_settings.py.erb template rather than being
parameterized, making it impossible for users to enable support for
these functions.  This patch adds a parameter hash to enable users to
select how they want to configure Neutron services and sets default
values to match the old hardcoded settings to maintain backward
compatibility.

Conflicts:
	manifests/init.pp
	spec/classes/horizon_init_spec.rb

Change-Id: Ibfa75a83a88d9bb26d65c026c7f913e000bce13f
Closes-Bug: #1274382
(cherry picked from commit e2c0e7543a3e73013101fc34567a1850367538b1)

commit_message:
XenAPI: Add the mechanism to attach a pci device to a VM.

 Before booting a VM we check if there are PCI devices reserved
by this VM and if there are any we attach them.

 A PCI device can be asked by a VM by choosing a flavor that
request PCI devices. See the wiki about pci passthrough for more
details:

https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Pci_passthrough#Create_a_flavor

 We are attaching a PCI device by adding a key "pci" to the
"other-config" parameter of a VM.

Change-Id: I4aca96b11f931f70cf6442adac64e867ce1affb6
Implements: blueprint pci-passthrough-xenapi

commit_message:
XenAPI: Add the support for updating the status of the host.

  We added a function into the xenhost plugin to get information
about PCI devices. Roughly we run the lspci command on dom0. This
information will be used to get the list of pci devices  that are
passed on the pciback.hide dom0 command line.

  The hide option is used to hide the devices from the normal guest
drivers and assign them to the pciback kernel driver at boot on dom0
instead of their normal driver. We will parse the output of the lspci
command to find which device is using the pciback kernel driver and
thus to know if it has been passed to the pciback.hide option.

  This information will be used to perform the match with the
list of pci devices provided in pci_whitelist into /etc/nova/nova.conf.

Implements: blueprint pci-passthrough-xenapi

Change-Id: I465fc5d29f3c47ab0079adcfcc2d7d6501bd4b20

commit_message:
Add systemd notification support to heat

This mirrors work done in other OpenStack projects
to add systemd notification support to signal that
a given process is ready to accept requests.

The heat-api, heat-api-cfn, heat-engine, and
heat-api-cloudwatch processes are all covered by
a new, single, 'onready' configuration file option.

Additionally, the sample configuration file has been
updated to match.

Implements: blueprint systemd-integration

Change-Id: I90d2b915e2568a65ed9ed78923c9982e19f9c948
Signed-off-by: Lon Hohberger <lhh@redhat.com>

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-15 09:06:49.000000000', 'files': ['savanna/openstack/common/db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

Closes-bug: #1276510

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

Change-Id: I006fd3ae88dd7ab61f7f8811562fb78ce4a331ad
"}]
commit_message:
Don't raise MySQL 2013 'Lost connection' errors

Closes-bug: #1276510

Although this code error is part of the `ping_listener` tests, it was
missing from the list of known - and ignored - connection errors.

The code error 2013 refers to a connection lost during a query, see:
https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/error-messages-client.html#error_cr_server_lost

Without this error code, the session won't try to reconnect to mysql,
which makes `max_retries` useless.

Change-Id: I006fd3ae88dd7ab61f7f8811562fb78ce4a331ad

Almost every object thus far has done this in refresh():

Change-Id: Iced009f7ede969a9ad01f2dae4d003a3d2dcb8d5

commit_message:
Clean up duplicated code in objects

Almost every object thus far has done this in refresh():

for field in self.fields:
    if (hasattr(self, base.get_attrname(field)) and
              self[field] != current[field]):
          self[field] = current[field]

it can be taken in the base.py like:

def change_obj_fields(self, current):
    for field in self.fields:
        if (hasattr(self, get_attrname(field)) and
                  self[field] != current[field]):
              self[field] = current[field]

Change-Id: Iced009f7ede969a9ad01f2dae4d003a3d2dcb8d5

commit_message:
Setting to use syslog in Murano added.

* Local logs added
* Logrotate configured
* Typos
* murano_use_syslog -> use_syslog
* murano_debug -> debug
* murano_verbose -> verbose
* syslog_log_facility
* murano user/group added back
* use bool values for debug/use_syslog
* applied diff with 74420

Replaces review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/62853/
Replaces review https://review.openstack.org/#/c/63705/

Change-Id: I9011d008d34ddc31c2fd7cc426cf63f2acd0c2db
Closes-Bug: 1261477

commit_message:
Implement user-defined tenant for neutron nets

Default networks were previously hardcoded to use
"admin" as the tenant, regardless of user input.
This patch is a workaround because nailgun creates
neutron_config with admin tenant hardcoded as well.

FIXMEs were added to indicate what code needs cleanup
after nailgun is patched.

Change-Id: I272b53b6dbb4e972f94e82e81b58920351f4144d
Partial-Bug: #1267431

commit_message:
Change bind address to use Identity endpoint host

Allow the bind interface address to take precendence, but default
to binding to the host attribute of the Identity API endpoint.
This brings the identity cookbook into conformance with the
other cookbooks regarding the service interface binding.

Closes-Bug: 1277266

Change-Id: I9634e2a359a6ce52b694859a7e84a57638bad5be

commit_message:
Backport to 4.0 following issues:

Closes-bug: #1279809

  #1275132 c82d4edd66701
  #1271274 244acdaab1050
  #1277112 078efe67207a4
  #1275132 7776ffe6fd94b6
  #1277147 0ba23e1a6a1a8c, 5fd706f58ab120b32
  #1274789 b8105f58bcb28
  #1278718 48e8c25aa484e

* Update l3_if_downup to eval carrier state when starting
* Allow more than two interfaces in the OVS bonds.
* FIX: incorrect condition in l23network bond type
* Fix un-changeable resource in l3_if_downup
* FIX: L23network module can't get one-element array as bond parameter
* FIX errors while print error massage.
* L23network: allow setup MTU in the network_schema
* Get Ordering of ifconfig operations from transformation order if it possible.

Change-Id: I2fa29b72188dc7798eaf9c388cf46b831a5a38c9

subject: Install syslinux also in nova-baremetal
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-14 15:39:43.000000000', 'files': ['elements/nova-baremetal/install.d/80-pxelinux'], 'message': 'Install syslinux also in nova-baremetal

Previously the element relied on nova installing syslinux
before implicitly, which was not always the case in package
install mode. Also install it where it is actually used. Now
it will be installed twice, which should normally not hurt
(works in my testing). A previous iteration with a mere move
was rejected (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/70718/).

Change-Id: I8b460beda4275eff5878031593ce3c15307e94c9
'}]
commit_message:
Install syslinux also in nova-baremetal

Previously the element relied on nova installing syslinux
before implicitly, which was not always the case in package
install mode. Also install it where it is actually used. Now
it will be installed twice, which should normally not hurt
(works in my testing). A previous iteration with a mere move
was rejected (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/70718/).

Change-Id: I8b460beda4275eff5878031593ce3c15307e94c9

commit_message:
libvirt: configuration element for a random number generator device

This configuration exposes a paravirtual random number generator device,
with a default backend set to a hosts /dev/random

An optional rate element can be provided in order to limit the consumption
of host's entropy by the guest.

Partially implements blueprint libvirt-rng-device
Change-Id: Id1be32a307473aec2ff0b54b43b2ca3547d74b84

Messaging backend selection

boot-stack's element dependencies.

The set_time_override function in timeutils was written as a
helper function to mock utcnow for unittests before 'mock' was
generally used. Now that we have mock and fixture, we no longer
need to use it.

commit_message:
tighter control of mq attribute defaults

remove repetitive copy/paste blocks that are developing drift (eg., qpid
'reconnect' missing for compute, rabbit 'ha' missing for image, and
rabbit 'use_ssl' missing for network).

this provides more reliable assignment of defaults and better visibility
of the one-off tweaks (eg., notification_topics).

Change-Id: Iba6fd99de86ea5ce5afab1654c4bc7e7d32f3e51

In a production system, the previous state-path would default to
something like /usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages. Not only is this a
bizarre place to keep Designate's state, it also breaks the bind9
backend, which attemps to create and write to
/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/bind9.

Since /var/lib is defined in the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard as the
place to store persistent state information, it's better to explicitly
use it as the default state-path.

Closes-bug: 1279989
"}]
commit_message:
Default state-path to /var/lib/designate

In a production system, the previous state-path would default to
something like /usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages. Not only is this a
bizarre place to keep Designate's state, it also breaks the bind9
backend, which attemps to create and write to
/usr/lib/python2.6/site-packages/bind9.

Since /var/lib is defined in the Filesystem Hierarchy Standard as the
place to store persistent state information, it's better to explicitly
use it as the default state-path.

Change-Id: I91922799ba1dcae1ad33f1abbec79b1eb907307f
Closes-bug: 1279989

commit_message:
Remove instruction setting ovs_use_veth to True

Remove instruction to set ovs_use_veth to True. Updated kernels shipped
to RDO/RHELOSP, and in RHEL/CentOS 6.5, mean that this is no longer
required. The updated kernels support network namespaces properly.

Change-Id: I6d34f924c1d93b6b7de2b0b7885755e48263a4d4
Closes-Bug: #1268806
backport: havana

commit_message:
Fix metering service endpoint path spec

After installing ceilometer with the metering cookbook, invoking the
ceilometer CLI fails because the API base URL used is
http://127.0.0.1:8777/v1/v2 which means that the base endpoint path of
/v1 is incorrect and it should be simply /.

The openstack-common cookbook was updated to set the right path but we
need to update the test cases, and point to the new version of the
common cookbook.

Change-Id: I203a5a6346a3765bb249149a209122ec3d33601d
Partial-Bug: #1277742

commit_message:
Sync request_id, request_utils for cinder

This is in preparation for work being done on request ID tracing across
OpenStack services.

Per discussion in blueprint cross-service-request-id , the standard header
name for the request ID across OpenStack projects should be
x-openstack-request-id. The request_id middleware was created for just this
purpose, as oslo change Ic7967cd62e7b743343d70f751b9238339171e013 . Using the
same middleware allows for consistency across projects.

There is an additional oslo module, request_utils, introduced as
change Id085c4444fee2bb68b80738bfe77ccb0ba1908ec to allow uniform logging of
request IDs. Bring that in as well so we have it when necessary.

Implements: blueprint add-standard-req-id-header
Change-Id: If080df2a323347924c93a912538dab5ffeffe982

commit_message:
Pass instance name to neutron port create on boot

bug 1175211

Using neutron dhcp agent the VM hostname does not
match the DNS name. Neutron writes dnsmasq config
file using the instances ip address with (dots
replaced with dashes) and the dhcp_domain name.
This causes issues on the instance (instance can't
look up it's own hostname).

Changing network/neutronv2/api.py to pass instance
name as port name to neutron port create.
This will provide neutron the ability to lookup
the port name that was set and write the dnsmasq
config file using the port name.

The relevant change in neutron is in:
Change-Id: I4107d00dab29f0e4945d90fa68dbe7d84277c296

Change-Id: Ida57222fa41b345626b8c8bcf3be32ceb757b4fb

commit_message:
Implement retype in HP LeftHand driver

This adds the ability to modify the
type of an existing HP LeftHand volume to
another type supported on the same backend.

Main use case for this is changing provisioning,
(full vs. thin), adaptive optimization and data
protections settings for a volume on-demand.

Change-Id: I78e53431708bcb3151c5dc4016e65d1a655e03c6
Implements: blueprint retype-support-for-hplefthand-driver

commit_message:
Make the single entrypoint for client

It's a common approach to have such common Client with the following
path: "someclient.client.Client".

It contains mapping from client/API version to the class that handles it.

This change will make us able to perform any refactoring inside the client
w/o need to change paths in all projects that are using Savanna client.

Change-Id: I7d0237591ed7beccbd43fe60ce3b6cfc522fcf31
